        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 2:18PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 218 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Boncarbo, or 14 miles northwest of Trinidad. This thunderstorm was
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boncarbo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
